description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM UNTIL 31.03.2022 DUE TO THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Specialist Nurse for Looked After Children and Care Leavers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We would like to invite applicants for the above post based in North Wales. The area offers coastal and rural locations and Chester and the Northwest are easily accessible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will work within the Looked After Children&#39;s (LAC) team for Conwy and Denbighshire North Wales. The post holder will have Professional responsibility to coordinate timely completion and implementation of high quality statutory health assessments and care plans for a specific cohort of Looked After Children. With a focus on preventing family breakdown and supporting family reunification where appropriate. The aim and purpose of the post is to provide services in partnership with multi-disciplinary teams within and outside of Betsi Cadwaladr University Health Board; to ensure that LAC are able to access the health services they require through early identification of additional needs and referral. The post holder will be an advocate for Looked Children and Care Leavers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The base for the post will be discussed at interview and there will be instances where post-holders will be able work from home.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To apply for this opportunity you will need to be an &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NMC Registered Nurse and in addition hold a Health Visitor / School Nurse/CAMHS or Paediatric Nursing Qualification (Degree or equivalent).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications for secondment will be considered with the agreement of your current Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Health Board offers:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Great education and development opportunities, thanks to our close links with our local Universities, along with induction, orientation and preceptorship, we will make sure you are supported to enhance your skills through continuing professional development. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working to suit you and your family, to enable you to achieve a great work-life balance. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free Flu vaccination &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hepatitis B vaccination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Health Support network&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS Discounts i.e. Restaurants, retail, package holidays&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carys Williams / Sharon Gammon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Manager / Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;carys.williams3@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
